profile_data.summary:
I am a Data Science Graduate Student at the University at Buffalo. I am actively seeking Data Science and Machine Learning internship opportunities for Spring 2022/ full-time effective July 2022. 

The boundless possibility of exploring new things has always kept my inquisitive mind engrossed. Proactive in my approach to learning, I found a new interest, Artificial-Intelligence after coming across my Android phone’s feature of Google’s Text-To-Speech Converter that guided me towards Natural Language Processing. Since then, I have been exploring and growing in the Data Science and ML domain.

Presently I am a Data Science Master’s student at the University at Buffalo – SUNY having three years of professional experience in the relevant field with Infosys LTD and ThirdEye Data Analytics Pvt. Ltd.

Simultaneously active participation in a wide range of extra-curricular activities has ensured my gregarious personality. Love for music and passion for literary activities like Sudoku compelled me to participate in the cultural fests. Recently, I have grown a new interest in Kayaking and have been really enjoying doing so. 

Competencies: data science, machine learning, Python, Tableau, Artificial Intelligence, PySpark

If you have a project I can work on, please reach out to me at sanchari.gautam@gmail.com.

A company has been potentially hacked and we aim to find out the types of hackers that have caused the threat. We have valuable data about the hacks, including information like session time, locations, wpm typing speed, etc. The forensic department has also provided us with the meta-data of each session that the hackers used to connect to their servers. We have worked here with such attributes to find out the potential group of hackers.
Skills used: PySpark, Databricks Notebook, K-Means Clustering Algorithm
